Whether parked at our camp or traveling around the playa, the Castle Anomalous mutant vehicle is the core of our theme camp and our community interactiong
fields.name: Castle Anomalous

fields.description: Celestial Bodies is a straight-friendly camp hosting a large and comfortable lounge for shade, drinks, music and entertainment. Visit our Garden of Hedon art installation and dust off your 80’s attire (disco drag always encouraged) and/or your favorite underwear for a DevaLution disco extravaganza.
fields.name: Celestial Bodies

fields.description:
Come dance your ass off with the dancetronauts....
 We have all the great stuff you need to Relax, Recharge, Or go crazy!
fields.name: Center of gravity

fields.description: CEREAL THRILLERS CEREAL BAR! Enjoy a bowl of the cereals you loved as a child or our special playa cereal cocktails. Mornings, about 8 to noon.
fields.name: Cereal Thrillers

fields.description: Chaos, joy, good conversation - Gold Parade at our camp Wednesday afternoon.  Assemble at 4:30 to work on costumes, parade at 5:00.  Bring your best gold finery, particularly shiny gold.  If you don’t have a gold costume we will do our best to deck you out.  Cocktails after the parade.
fields.name: Children of Chaos Farewell Tour

fields.description: Chop Shop is a small Playa Neighborhood Garage that is ready to help all modes of playa transportation with parts,repair,and advice. While you visit our shop, you'll enjoy our special sarcasm about bad playa bicycles, the Shade Chill Spot, the Daily Chop Shop Specials and service with a smile.
fields.name: Chop Shop

fields.description: The Church of Respect is a non denominational, non judgmental, pro inclusionist congregation of lovely souls wishing to spread the word of respect. Respect for oneself and for others. This year we celebrate with a commitment/marriage ceremony open to all and our Saskatini Cocktail Shaker night.
fields.name: Church of Respect

fields.description: Camp Circus Jerk promotes evolution through gay spirit, which we believe encompasses a variety of sexual passions and psychology. Run away with our circus and get "more gay" through public meditation, tantra, erotic workshops, group exploration, and performance art!
fields.name: Circus Jerk

fields.description: Stilt craziness and live music.  The home-zone of Dookie Doodle (a BRC irreverent novelty band) and Mojo Green (Reno's funkajazzadelic quintet), along with stilters from Reno to the Bay Area.  Even more cliche' than last year!
fields.name: Cirque du Cliche'

fields.description: We run the famous Playa Speed dating every night at dusk.... four guys, four girls, eitht minutes, one intense time! Alternative lifestyle versions too.
fields.name: Clevian

fields.description: Club Verboten returns for a very special 10th anniversary week.All of the favorite Verboten retro avant-garde dances will be offered to The Popular Masses at a convenient time and location.
fields.name: Club Verboten

fields.description: Specializing in free fittins' and chauvinist clown performance, the Cock 'n Waffle is a great place to stop by and give those legs a rest.
fields.name: Cock 'n Waffle

fields.description: Bleary-eyed and zombified from last night adventures? Portland Based Coffee Zombies animate you, the walking dead. As the sun rises, so do we with the freshest pot of morning coffee as only Portland knows how to brew it.
fields.name: Coffee Zombies

fields.description: A place of refuge for nomadic mountain deviants, the Conscious Monkey Clan unites to sound its battle cry far and wide across the playa galaxy. Inspired by Eastern wisdom and the power of Jah, the notorious Madame Astrolabe and her pillaging monkey crew, seduce all those ensnared in her booming wake.
fields.name: Conscious Monkey Clan

fields.description: Ever wonder what would happen if a large group of people merged their creativity to produce miraculous pieces of artwork.  Wonder no more, just stop by and see what comes into being.  Bring your creativity and become part of the process. (If you lack an imagination one may be provided for you)
fields.name: Consensual Art Camp

fields.description: Cool Aid Oasis does it again!  We're back with our "Magic Cool Aid" and ready to treat you!  We have ICE TREATS and COOL AID for everyone to enjoy.  Come chill with us, but beware; Watch for flying SNO-BALLS!!!
fields.name: Cool Aid Oasis

fields.description: An oasis in the desert, open while it's sunny out. CoolTown has a fully misted 400sq.ft. community shade structure to chill, rest, relax, and socialize or use our self service misting station.  We have body/hair rinsing mornings and afternoons. Snow cones occasionally served.
fields.name: CoolTown

fields.description:
Cosmic Elves was seeded in the frequency of the BC westcoast tribal dance
community and the LA Gathering of the Tribes in Black Rock City in 2003.
Representing this intentional dance community consists of a collection of allied 
tribes from across the continent
fields.name: Cosmic Elves

fields.description: Cosmic Recess is a playground with a space theme.  We believe creativity, play and lightheartedness are neccesary components for happiness and joy!  All of our playground elements are original and homemade (most with recycled/reused materials).  Having fun and connecting with each other is our goal!!
fields.name: Cosmic Recess / Lustre Village

fields.description: CouchSurfing Camp creates a space where weary wild and wondrous travelers are always welcome. This camp is about "CouchSurfing" around the world and we are all members of the CouchSurfing.org project; Come sit and enjoy the MutantSofa and learn how CouchSurfing can change the world!
fields.name: CouchSurfing Camp

fields.description: Who doesn't love a Lil' Crackwhore?  We will teach you how to properly work the streets in this tough economy.
fields.name: Crackwhore Camp

fields.description: The Crown Collective is the home port for the playa's own Mississippi riverboat, The Lady Sassafras.Departing daily for musical adventures into the artistic heart of Burning Man, and nightly for intergalactic journeys through the universe of funk, blues, and jazz.
fields.name: Crown Collective

fields.description:
We're coming to devastate you.  That's all.
Pure trash...ALL THE TIME!
fields.name: DUSTFISH

fields.description: DFT is back in Black Rock and says Howdy! Texans, Non-Texans, ex-pats, Texans that never lived here yet, those who’ve never been here but like beer, and everyone else, please stop by. We're in Gigsville again and I guess we’ll bring a flag or something. Come sit a spell—the pilloasis awaits....
fields.name: Damn Fucking Texans

fields.description: Join the Darweenie Camp for a Weenie Roast on Tuesday & Thursday.  There will be food, fun & gaity to be had by all!
fields.name: DarWeenie Camp

fields.description: Dive into the Darwin Fish Tank;here you can drink the water, snack on some fish food and beat the heat with our cool misting system for a genuine underwater adventure. When you are ready to grow a pair (of legs that is!) climb out of the primordial ooze and move on to the next phase of your evolution
fields.name: Darwin Fish Tank

fields.description: Come join in the minty fun at DeMentha. You'll find great tunes from our DJ line-up, lovingly prepared fresh mojitos, aromatherapy, ample shade and plenty of cooling mist. Combined with a hearty welcome you've got the perfect recipe for a good time. 1-5pm daily. Dark Wednesday.
fields.name: DeMentha

fields.description: Committed to the playful, creative exploration of the individual and collective psyche, Deep Psychx offers workshops and a safe haven for participatory expressive arts.  Journey towards wholeness whilst making new friends and beautifying the Playa!
fields.name: Deep Psychx

fields.description: Den 010-  "Service Above (and Below) All Else."
fields.name: Den 010

fields.description: The Den of Iniquity is a protected space for leather and goth participants interested in learning about and participating in select aspects of bondage and SM play. Guests are invited to come experience the deeply erotic, expressive and creative safe haven that is the Den.
fields.name: Den of Iniquity

fields.description: Our camp is Pink.  We make Pink stuff.  We decorate with Pink.  We wear Pink.  We like the color Pink.  We are the Department of Pink Works.  Participate in our Pink Parade, where you can "Show Pink."  Come on over and pose for a photo with Glenda the Good Pink Witch.  Look for the Pink camp.
fields.name: Department of Pink Works DPinkW

fields.description: Abundant afternoon shade, comfy couches, chilly lemonade and iced tea, great music, dancing and fire spinning, figure drawing and other art events, and of course, our jumbo games: Rock Yer Balls and the Fling of Destiny! Also, Playa home of Spirit's Fire! Come evolve with us!! It is your Destiny!!
fields.name: Destiny Lounge

fields.description: DP Camp (yes, that's intentional) is designed to give adults a chance to relive their youth through games, activities and varieties of play.  Come visit our bar, clubhouse and playground.  Look for our events in the What/When/Where.
fields.name: Deviant Playground

fields.description:
Expand your inner vision while indulging your senses... a soothing treatment of refreshing eye drops, cucumber slices and a cooling facial gel-pack...
followed by a meditative lavender-scented eye-pillow surrounded by the enchanting healing powers of the Dilated Peoples Eye Spa.
fields.name: Dilated Peoples Eye Spa

fields.description: Come on in, sit under the mister,listen to some Zappa . Yeah..THAT kind of dirty love. Although it's not like we dislike the other kind or anything.
fields.name: Dirty Love Camp

fields.description:
Dover School Board
Drawing the connection between our dark past and our enlightened future.
Join us in having fun creating a time lapse drawing.
We will provide all the tools you provide your imagination.
fields.name: Dover School Board

fields.description: Dr. Carl's big board of stuff is imposing, daunting and a little bit sexy. Pick something from our big board, go out and find that something. Return to us, convince an official that you deserve a fantastic reward...collect a fantastic reward.
fields.name: Dr. Carl's Dept. of Collections

fields.description: As a tadpole changes into a frog, Dr. Fate's Moving Potion Palace now takes its show on the road to purvey all-natural restorative tonics to wayward wanderers and wanton women of Black Rock City.  Spin The Wheel to guide you to your curative concoction and discover your fate for the evening.
fields.name: Dr. Fate's Potion Palace

fields.description: Community Drum Circle, all ages and skill levels. One hour before sunset until one hour after, monday thru friday only.
fields.name: Drums on the Playa

fields.description: An interactive artwork where participants express their emotions and thoughts by spraying dyes and pigments on a translucent tent-like canvas. The installation continuously evolves; the applied colors glowing at night from interior light. Colorful libations and commentary help to inspire passersby.
fields.name: Dyenamic Huephoria!
EE Camp: Magic Circus Band Camp

fields.description:
EVILution ~ City of Fallen Angels
Friday Night EVIL-steria Festival: A Masked carnival, enjoy goblets of red wine, entertainment, Laughing & Dancing...

Play Croquet threw our "Garden of Heathens"
fields.name: EVILution ~ City Of Fallen Angels

fields.description: Earth Tribe is back on the playa and we've gone BRZRK.  Past Earth Tribe camp members and fellow burners please stop by, say hello and enjoy a break in our chill dome.
fields.name: Earth Tribe Gone BRZRKR

fields.description: The Garden of Eden is the place where it all began.  The place where man and woman first tasted of the tree of the Knowledge of Good and Evil.  In the theme of Evolution this is where participants can come and have their photo taken framed by the backdrop of the Garden and tasting of the tree.
fields.name: Eden
El Circo and The Do Lab

fields.description: Relax with us as we take a starship ride into a furry, laser-lit future filled with love, danger and adventure!
fields.name: Electric Barbarella

fields.description: Elk Lodge: Flora & Fauna is an all femaale reclamation of male-centric institutions- the evolution of the "old boy's club". All genders welcome to our feminist pub [expect adoration or heckling, depending on our mood].
fields.name: Elk Lodge: Flora & Fauna

fields.description:
Getting Married at BM???  Stop by Empress Rosa's self-service Wedding Palace.
Rings, certificates, seating for 20-30, legal wedding services available with  
prior planning.  Located within Terminal City.  Open 24/7  First Come, First Serve!
fields.name: Empress Rosa's Wedding Palace

fields.description: The mission of Entheon Village is to demonstrate a future in which sustainability, ecological responsibility, environmental stewardship, and meditative and mystical consciousness are a welcomed and integrated part of society, and where art, spirituality and creativity is central to that vision.
fields.name: Entheon Village

fields.description: Come chillax and chat with the good peeps at Equilibrium.  Be sure to say hello to Michael.
fields.name: Equilibrium

fields.description: Everywhere land is a collection of friends from Canada, the U.S., Australia and Italy. Drop by and visit everywhere!
fields.name: Everywhere Land

fields.description:
Stop by EvoLOTION day or night for a self-serve helping of moisturizers and other creams. Sunscreen for the days. Heating lotion for the nights. Aloe for burns.
And show up for our special events of full-service lotion application.
Do you have some spare lotions? Email us or donate on the playa!
fields.name: EvoLOTION

fields.description:
You say you want an evolution?  How about a cafe' that offers coffee, newspapers & conversation by
day and morphs into a Beatles-oriented blacklight Octopus' Garden by night? Cafe' hosted by Lucy, in the Sky, with Diamonds. Location: Nowhere, man. Come together, right now! All you need is...coffee!
fields.name: Evolution #9 Cafe'

fields.description: We chill and boogie out on inflatable things up like inner tubes, pool toys, and blow up dolls. In our pimped lounge area you can float on air, dance to a DJ, or read thought provoking books.
fields.name: Expansion Mansion

fields.description: Honoring those fallen off the Tangled Bank, and leading the Extinct Creatures parade Wednesday. Also daily reading aloud of Darwin's Origin of Species.
fields.name: Extinct Creatures

fields.description: F.U.N. (Fucked Up Nutrition) Camp has been part of Martini Village for the past 8 years.  Come imbibe with alcohol or not.  Refresh, revive, and repeat – bring your own cup!
fields.name: F.U.N. Camp

fields.description:
Fallout Shelter
Welcome and Escape the elements in our 16x32   Military tent while listening to rock music and have a cooool drink, YES, with ice. We light up the night with sound chasing lights and other eye candy. Enjoy spirits mixed by Frank and Jose,They make a Mean Playa Passion.
fields.name: FALLOUT SHELTER

fields.description: The Fandando Village welcomes the return of Funkcamp, the crew who brought the Church of Funk to us in 2002.  We'll have the live funk groove, as well as events like Bootie: Black Rock City and Backstage Pass!  And the Black Rock Broadcasting Corporation will be bringing it all to you live.
fields.name: Fandango

fields.description: With all the excitement of a sideshow carnival.our performance stage will let everyone be a Star,providing interactive games to delight with all the thrills and spills for our bike friendly enthusiast !
fields.name: Fantasy Funhouse & Wheel of Karma

fields.description:
Through the creative and concsious efforts of its members, Fixxxation
Station arrives on the Black Rock Playa.  Thriving on a common goal of
Community interactivity:  Fixxxation Station provides BRC with an environment
That stimulates the senses and soul.  Doing so through interactive art,
music, yoga, massage, conversation and libations.
fields.name: Fixxxation Station

fields.description: Are Mimosa's just for brunch? Hell NO!... We've got DJ's, a flowing Champagne and Juice bar, fire dancing, and freaks of fun just for your pleasure XOXOXO.
fields.name: Fiz Juice!

fields.description: The Free Movement Zone is bringing something extra to the Playa this year. Something you've never seen before! Forget everything you know about dance. Forget everything you know about poles. Operation Polegasm will change you ForEver! So come on over, grab a Pole, and have a Gasm!
fields.name: Free Movement Zone

fields.description: Free Photography Zone has been photographing the participants of Burning Man in a studio setting since 1996 providing each person photographed with a print to memoralize thier time at BM.  Additionally a gallery of previous years photographs are displayed and given away at the end of each years BM.
fields.name: Free Photography Zone

fields.description: Holy sanctuary for beings awakening to oneness, tantric non-dual sacred space for open hearted lovers, shamanic ecstatic Kundalini dance, satsang, and yoga. Experience love-bliss bodily, move into seventh stage life with Master Free Lovelight Starseed Dreamdancer Shunyatananda Nataraja.
fields.name: Free Tribe-Tantra Temple

fields.description: TripKnight and LawyersforBurners.com proudly announce their ensemble performance for Burning Man 2009: FreeStyle Palace: Evolution of the Black Rock City Allstars.  FreeStyle Palace 2009 will operate a sound stage featuring nightly hip hop shows with the Allstars from sunset to about 2:00 am nightly.
fields.name: FreeStyle Palace

fields.description: Freedom Lounge offers a list of Organic Spiritual freedoms including Alignments, removal of personal heaviness, dream interpretation, a cup of English tea, the best coffee you will ever have and great "Craic" (Gaelic for conversation) relaxing and comforting.
fields.name: Freedom lounge

fields.description: Frogma is the little theme camp that could, where everyone is your friend and neighbor! Hop on over to our lily pads Monday through Thursday at 5:00pm for BRC's one and only Hoppy Hour. Serving up ice cold slushy Frogaritas in our dome sweet dome. You're guaranteed to make a rainbow of connections.
fields.name: Frogma

fields.description: Stop by or stake your habitation at this homage to the eclectic world of wonder.  We encourage the aerial arts of silks, tissu, cord de lisse in additon to juggling in all its wondrous forms.  We will have many tools for these off-circus arts on hand, including rigging, but please also bring some.
fields.name: From Silks to Medicine Sticks

fields.description: Funky town will have live dj sets and plenty of yard games.  We will be working with the robot heart crew to provide plenty of fun and drinks for all day and night.
fields.name: Funky Town

fields.description:
GATO is a fun loving group hailing from San Francisco
A 'Family of Friends'
And when you come to our camp
YOU are family!
fields.name: GATO

fields.description: On the playa since 2001. Our art car, the Floating Palace of Pleasure has been bumpin’ funky beats on the Playa since 2002.  Relax to down tempo chill grooves in the afternoon before an evening on our art-car. We’re an eclectic collection of individuals committed to spreading peace, love, and dance on the Playa as well as in our everyday lives.
fields.name: Garage Mahal

fields.description: In years past we've studied cultures - both foreign and familiar - as inspiration for theme camps such as Bollywood, Japanorama, La Dolce Vita, Sagrada and Home. This year, spurred by evolution, Dragon Debris will present a colorful effusion of illumination and texture, a Garden of DeLights.
fields.name: Garden of DeLights

fields.description: the gathering of the sphere is a group of old and new burners alike, brought together on a quest to come together on our own small sphere within the context of the countless others that surround us.
fields.name: Gathering of the Sphere

fields.description: A think tank of evolution psychic that can transcend your concious and lead you back to your animal roots.  Learn what animal you evolved from and let our resident artist take you on a journey back to your roots by transforming your outer soul into the inner soul you once were with body paints.
fields.name: Gay Rd Village

fields.description: We play with fire, do tricks for treats, take pictures of just about everything, then laugh some more. Stop on by & visit our wild west saloon! Warm your tush by one of our giant burn barrels and stand in AWE of the Great Theresa the nitrous demon!
fields.name: Gedi Prime

fields.description: Boy? Girl? Ze? Unidentified? You decide. Come blend it up and explore gender while drinking smoothies. This theme camp is designed for gender blending newbies, long time gender benders, and those of us that just want to experiment. Enjoy safe space workshops, costumes, yoga, body sculpting, beverages, music & more!
fields.name: Gender Blender

fields.description: The Northwest is an ever-changing landscape of ever-changing beings. Where and how we originated we don't truly know, but we must move forward with nature's cycle. Come see how evolution has impacted wine, skin care, shade, and community from the land of rain in our space of old and new beginnings.
fields.name: Genesis

fields.description: Serving cocktails by Intelligent Design, in honor of God's 7 days of creation with themed drinks. Join us every day from 2:00 to 4:00 pm for a delicious and drunken journey through Genesis. Come sit and relax in the shade, while enjoying such drinks as "Let there be Light" or "Land and Sea".
fields.name: Genesis: The Creationist Bar

fields.description: At Genital Portrait Studio, highly trained photographers offer you the opportunity capture that special side of yourself in the privacy of our playa studio. Your session may include a number of props and positions, and you can walk away with your very own Genital ID card.
fields.name: Genital Portrait Studio

fields.description: Gigsville is supporting this year's theme of Devolution by devolving into whatever it is that Gigsville has devolved into.  Please plan accordingly.
fields.name: Gigsville

fields.description: Gnome Camp is home to the Gnome Adoption Agency, where worthy parents receive an adorable garden gnome along with a disposable digital camera to record its adventures. Check out the gnome-capades on gnomecamp.com!
fields.name: Gnome Camp

fields.description: Sign the Oath of Secrecy, write in the Book of Confession, be purified by didjeridu and enter deep within the Lair of the Mystic Toad to open the mysterious God Box and reveal the secret contents within. The God Box has been providing equal opportunity mystical experience to BRC since 2003.
fields.name: God Box

fields.description: Hailing from the DC area and beyond, we offer several activities for your delight: sock poi making workshops, beginning poi spinning classes, hoop-making, beginner hoop lessons, a performance by members of the Playa Del Fuego Fire Conclave and more! Also a BRC Post Office 2.0 auxiliary mail drop.
fields.name: Great Balls of Fire & Post Office

fields.description: Ahoy there mates...this camp is where the Fishing Vessel (F/V) Gypsy Queen and its crew will dock, in between fishing periods of burner catch and release using our 100 fathom net. Come join us on the rolling playa, or celebrate your booty at our Gypsy Bar and Black Light Lounge.
fields.name: Gypsy Fleet

fields.description: Join the Gypsy Witches for our 10th year on the playa.  We have Salsa@Six and will be a meeting grounds for lesbians on the playa.  Check your What Where When for more info!
fields.name: Gypsy Witch Camp

fields.description: DAAAARRRRRWIN based his darrrrned theories on our hairrrrry arrrrrsses. Lookin Farrrward to farrhh raughrrr   barghhh narr and drawrrr....        YAR!
fields.name: H.M.S. Nautitickle

fields.description: At Hot Wheelz Camp, we offer the gift of mobility to fellow Burners who might have difficulty traveling to the far reaches of Black Rock City. It is our goal to expand and enhance the opportunities for our Themecamp guests to PARTICIPATE!
fields.name: HOT WHEELZ CAMP

fields.description: The Hammock Hangout is a giant 12,000 square foot passive solar shade structure with dozens of hammocks and an all day karaoke lounge underneath.
fields.name: Hammock Hangout & RV[IP} Lounge

fields.description: Weary from trekking an unparalleled melange of earthly and heavenly beauty?  The Hang-Out is the place to recharge. Hammocks. Shade. Good company. Open all day and all night.  Just lay down!  Maybe you can Cum join us for a morning of naked erotica readings from the Birdcage. We scratch itches!
fields.name: Hang-Out

fields.description: This is HAPPY CAMP! We like to help people be HAPPAY!!!
fields.name: Happy Camp

fields.description: Hardly Davidson Cafe.  Stop by and have your bike cut/welded and modified to chopper status.  Have a drink and watch some classic biker flicks on the big screen.
fields.name: Hardly Davidson Cafe

fields.description: Heaven's Ghetto, where working just good enough is a virtue.  Come enjoy the spiritual Teeter Totter of Death, let your inner tagger out on our Graffitti walls or chill our dome and smoke a hookah.
fields.name: Heaven's Ghetto

fields.description: Hippocampus is a memory making machine in your brain and on the playa.  Stop by and see what memories you can make.
fields.name: Hippocampus

fields.description: Hokey Pokey Camp Man or Monkey   Dance The Hokey Pokey at noon daily-Friends of Bill W. meeting at 5 daily.  Largest Take One Leave One north of the south pole. This is 24 hour Camp.  Everyone welcome.
fields.name: Hokey Pokey Camp Man or Monkey

fields.description: A Home Brewers Community where brewers of the Playa can meet and share. Hand crafted beer, mead soda and wine all celebrated cold in the shade. Bring your home brewed keg and we'll refrigerate, tap, give credit,discuss it and enjoy W/BRC. RSVP please. We are old school B.M. Open, community, low tech
fields.name: Home Brew 4A Home Brew

fields.description: Why evolve when you can regress? Thwart away those feelings of insecurity by getting your dose of complimentary compliments and affirmations.
fields.name: Homeland InSecurity

fields.description: Homeslice - A slice of Home
fields.name: Homeslice

fields.description: Honi Soit is back on the playa to celebrate being banned from the Texas, Kansas, AND Arkansas school systems.  Our method of natural selection (cogitating cold can choices) truly demonstrates survival of the fittest!  Join the Order of the Garter for croquet, drinks, music, mist, and hat parties!
fields.name: Honi Soit Croquet Club

fields.description: Hookah Homestead is your place on the playa for an evening chill out and some puffs on the hookah.  Come chill out with us every night from 5-8 and select sunrise sets.  Unique flavors and good company!
fields.name: Hookah Homestead

fields.description:
Horny Camp: the fabulous interactive camp where you can make your own set of playa-horns.  We provide the clay, the gas oven, chill house beats, and shade in the mid day sun.  If you are already horny, that’s OK, we can help you with that too!

Classes M-Th, 12PM-ish to 4PM-ish, unless we’re hangover in which case you never know…
fields.name: Horny Camp!

fields.description: Human Frolic Project is all about kicking up your heels, forgetting the default world and embracing the freedom of Black Rock City. Our lounge will be hosting 'Welcome Home' parties, on Mon, Tues and Wed pm, with an open bar daily for playa sojourners needing a sip of strength. Corner of 6:00 & G
fields.name: Human Frolic Project

fields.description: Evolve into a Glamorous Being, adapted to feel good and look great on the Playa.  Our services, if you are lucky enough for them to be rendered, include massage, playa-hair, anti-chaffing powder, spray-downs and makeup.  Have a cocktail and beautify your playa evolution experience, Humboldt style...
fields.name: Humboldt Beauty Bar

fields.description: Hushville, an aural oasis in chaotic BRC, is open to any camper who pre-registers and can abide our three simple rules: 1) No generators; 2) no amplified sound; and 3) Leave No Trace. We are host to large, solo, theme, and non-theme camps, and residents from all parts of the US, Canada, and Europe.
fields.name: Hushville

fields.description: Hometown:  Novato, CA
fields.name: Idle Hands

fields.description: At 15 years old Illumination Village is probably the oldest village on the playa! We are an active, driven community of dedicated artists, technologists and fans of fire. We stoke the flames, mixing fire and steel, keeping your body warm at night, and your eyes twinkling with the glow of combustion
fields.name: Illumination Village

fields.description: Feel your mind blow as you manipulate the Seizuredome with its Magic Hamster Ball!  Drink tea with a mermaid in the Agnostic Science Reading Room! Shake it to live improvised electronic music and live mixed video from the usual mad scientists!  EVOLVE, DAMMIT, EVOLVE!
fields.name: Image Node

fields.description: Sharing and Square Dancing.
fields.name: In Dust We Trust

fields.description: A group of artists who explore and document the fine art of playing with fire.  We specialize in capturing that moment of glee that comes with lighting a burst of fire.
fields.name: IncendiaryIntent

fields.description: the camp will be a comfy lounge and bar for people from everywhere to connect and mingle.
fields.name: Insomniac Cafe

fields.description: At the Interaction Cafe we do not serve food or drinks – we serve interactions. Perhaps you'd like to start off with a casual conversation for an appetizer, engage in an interactive game for an entree and end with a song for dessert while you drink in the moment.
fields.name: Interaction Cafe

fields.description:
Too much techno?  Not enough Fire?  Iron Rose answers with alternative music
and fire of our own for you to set by.  ...did someone say bluegrass?
fields.name: Iron Rose

fields.description:
The Island of the Lost Cupcakes is the home of the Sqysh Fysh mutant vehicle, and various
Klowny Shenanigans
fields.name: Island of the Lost Cupcakes

fields.description:
JOBI: Playground Games
Evolve! Find your inner schoolyard superstar! Recess is in! Enjoy playground classics like tetherball, foursquare, hopscotch, volleyball, leapfrog, kiss chase, duck duck goose, and many more. Bring a team or come play alone. Rules will be evaluated on a second-by-second basis.
fields.name: JOBI Playground Games

fields.description: Spiritual journeys, readings, healings and dream interpretations are what you can experience when you visit our theme camp. Let's not forget about the sno-cones! Sno-Cones offered daily! Come cool off and be refreshed in spirit and body!
fields.name: Journey's

fields.description: aMonkey'srEvolution. Does what seems to have changed only a rePresentation of the familiar?  Is the mud on the stone rolling down the hill changing the course of the universe or only a reassignment of location for a continued oeuvre? No matter how far the poo gets flung is anything really different for the monkey?  Jub Jub, one of your favoritely familiar of monkeys wonders perhaps that the more things change the more they stay the same.
fields.name: Jub Jub's Plastic Circus

fields.description: Traveling solo and tired of being far from the action? Want to camp closer to the esplanade or are you loner who wants to make new friends? "Just Show Up Camp!" is for individuals traveling solo who would like to "Just Show Up" and camp together without the usual formalities of a theme camp.
fields.name: Just Show Up Camp

fields.description: Why Kale? Because it's good for you. green beverages in the afternoon with minimal techno to jazz the soul.
fields.name: KAmp kaLE

fields.description: Bring your kamera and take your picture (along with your Burner buddies) with your faces in painted panels depicting the top five Kama Sutra positions (as voted on by the camp providers). See how you look in a new position you might like to try (that’s Evolution) or if it looks familiar, refresh your memory for another go soon.
fields.name: Kamera Sutra

fields.description: Kamp Kammaniwannalaya is a loose knit group of friends and family that enjoy and share the love of life and all it has to offer. We try our best to give back to the community all the joys we have recieved over the years.
fields.name: Kamp Kammaniwannalaya

fields.description: Kamp Suckie Fuckaye! Home of the Official Black Rock City Garnish fire conclave and the Suck and Fuck Saloon. Ground zero for KSF The Search For Neptune! Drink water... Suckie Fuckaaaaaaye!
fields.name: Kamp Suckie Fuckaye

fields.description: Sexy gnarly science for make benefit glorious nation of Kanuckistan.  "omne ignotum pro magnifico" -- "everything unknown appears magnificent"  Featuring Porno the Clown's Super Sex Freaks Side Show, Old Country Vodka Snorting Bar, 5th annual Xeni Cup street hockey tournament.  twitter.com/KRS7
fields.name: Kanuckistan Research Station

fields.description: Exercise your PCs!  Can you peg the Kegel-O-Meter?  New this year: Kegel Pong Video Game!  Compete for valuable bragging rights!  Exchange a piece of jewelry or just stop by for some tea.
fields.name: Kegel Kamp and Jewelry Exchange

fields.description: This will be the second year for Kentucky Fried to liven the mornings with Bourbon, Moonshine and our delicious smoked, fried Baloney Sandwiches. We served over 2000 last year. What better way to start your day than getting Fried the KFC way! Starting 9 AM each day.
fields.name: Kentucky Fried Camp

fields.description: KidsVille is THE place for children of all ages. We are a group of diverse families creating a unique space for play and other activities. Families with children 0-17 years of age are welcome to camp with us if they are pre-registered. Registration deadline is August 1st, 2009.
fields.name: KidsVille

fields.description:
Kimchi Camp 2009 - Now with more kimchi!

Heard of kimchi? Kimchi is a korean dish similar to sauerkraut but better tasting and smelling. Its ingredients are varied but it is always fermented. Come visit us for a DIY guide to making your own and maybe sample some if you dare.
fields.name: Kimchi Camp

fields.description: The Knarly Carnival is back again this year with our Big Moroccon Tent, a great shade from the sun and cool place to hang out and of course The Ice Cold Hard Cider, not to forget the smoked turkeys and soup!
fields.name: Knarly Carnival

fields.description: In NYrvana Village, visit our Mutation Station kostume dome.  Transformations by day, absurdity around the clock. Video, performances & evolutionary art. Costume recycling with your help (on playa or email us.).  Costuming the naked since 2001...
fields.name: Kostume Kult

fields.description: Hometown:  Goleta, UT
fields.name: Kroozr $kid Nation

fields.description: We are highly evolved Canadians with our kids and we are here to light up the night.
fields.name: L.E.D.'ers of the rEvolution

fields.description: Yes, the Lazy Ass folks are back again! We will not let GWB's recession kick our lazy asses! We'll have some familiar LAFers and some virgins LAFers. So come by, hang out, and show us your lazy ass. You'll be glad you did and so will we (|)
fields.name: LAFer Camp

fields.description: The Lava Lounge is a volcanic experience with lava, magma, and eruptions. Relax at the bar with a sip of volcanic punch, dance under the melting lava, be seduced by the erupitve forces of Mt. Luscious, or just enjoy the shade the shadow of the volcano casts by day.
fields.name: Lava Lounge

fields.description: Hometown:  Philadelphia, PA
fields.name: Lego Land

fields.description: Come visit the now legendary Pope Lenny O The Playa and his loyal minions as they wreak their very special brand of havoc from the friendly confines of Lenny Camp, situated within Redirection Connection Village. We're the secret substance that holds it all together.....come see how!
fields.name: Lenny Camp

fields.description: We are leopards of all ages.  Come join us for martinis that are as dry as the playa!  Serving Black Rock City since 1998.
fields.name: Leopard Martini Lounge

fields.description: Calling all Smartypants, Fact Freaks, Triviaholics, and the men & women who love them:  It’s Leopardy’s 3rd blockbuster year!  Group Quiz & Quaff -- 2:00-3:00; Leopardy! Game -- 3:00-4:00, Wednesday-Saturday. Wear puss print and bring the most underutilized organ at BRC -- your BRAIN!
fields.name: Leopardy Lair

fields.description: Look for the line of beautiful rocking chairs. There you will find ice cold sweet tea and canasta - the best card game known to man. Come chill out in our shade. As you enter our town you will be given a name tag and be treated as our life-long friend. This is where you belong, this is where you want to stay and relax. Come sit on our front porch!
fields.name: Lil Town

fields.description: Come witness the origin of life! Step up to Amino Acid Arcade. Pit yourself against games of chance & natural selection. Try your luck, head back to the bar-cade, "Origin of the Specious” & enjoy submitting to our utterly random, slightly humiliating (and possibly titillating) DIY genetic sequencing.
fields.name: Liminal Labs - Amino Acid Arcade

fields.description: Lollipop Shot Camp! This camp has evolved and now is a result of Natural Selection. "Survival of the Fittest" is our theme. Our glow in the dark shot glass has "mutated" and Darwin would be proud.  Shot Party celebrating your "personal evolution" on Thursday 6-9pm. Evolution playa wear encouraged.
fields.name: Lollipop Shot Camp

fields.description:
Representing loves evolutionary commitment to time, a Celtic inspired structure where 2 paths will become 1. Join us for the celebration Thurs o9o3o9 at dusk where after a short ceremony we will be hosting a party for all. Everyone welcome. Dress:Think Renaissance meets Mad Max
From:Vancouver Canada
fields.name: Love Knot

fields.description: Love Potion Camp welcomes you to a chill space full of art, creativity, whimsy, fun, family, positive vibes and Luurve. This is a non-sexual space but cuddling and BIG hugs are welcomed and encouraged.
fields.name: Love Potion Camp

fields.description: We are what you always wished a playground would be.  Complete with a bar, Love Puddle Playground offers kick-ass punch, tether ball, four square, detention, dildo jousting contests, and best of all, hugs.  "The bar is open!"
fields.name: Love Puddle Playground

fields.description: We are an art camp with a health outreach sideline we have constructed a (more durable) inflatable dome about 35 feet high, up as weather permits (usually limited, and only at night), and a sunset to sunrise light up disco floor. The health outreach part: 24/7 condom bar... please take up to ten.  :)
fields.name: Love to Bone

fields.description: Small group of friends who firmly believe in the robot army, apocalypse training, hummus love and of course, vaginas. Stop by our camp and enjoy some mimosas and hummus and our very popular, notorious even, cunt coloring book.
fields.name: Love-U-Lopian (Tube)

fields.description: 24hour village dedicated to PLAY. Home to Glittercamp, the Glitterbox 24 hour bar and groove station, Cosmic Recess, Chai Lovecamp - and proudly welcoming CostCo soulmate trading outlet for 2009! Daily glittering by Glittercamp, find your soul mate at CostCo, Cosmic Recess playground
fields.name: Lustre Village

fields.description: The MUTANT ALIEN BEAUTY SPA is a camp at Burning Man. FACE and BODY PAINTING will be done by an artist who has been trained in women’s airbrush make up. Anything from GEISHA with Lotus Blossoms to RAGING FLAMES and 'realistic' ALIEN skins will be offered, and a variety of face designs and masks.
fields.name: MUTANT ALIEN BEAUTY SPA

fields.description: Mad Flava brings you big playa taste, from your tounge to your feet, through Jonny & the Ho's mobile noodle cart to the 3rd annual BRC 5k run(Thurs 8am Center camp), we’ll make the Atkins diet our bitch while satiating your need for speed.
fields.name: Mad Flava!

fields.description: We are a group of Mages dedicated to evolution and comfort.  To that end, our camp offers from snacks and breathing cloths to seminars on divination and meditation.
fields.name: Mage Camp

fields.description: Tropical paradise comes to BRC.  Stop by and enjoy a cold margaritta in a tropical setting complete with music, misters, plenty of good company and fun.  Grab the mic and sing along if the mood hits you.  The Tiki Bar is expected to be open 12 noon til 6 pm.
fields.name: Margarittaville

fields.description: Welcome to the next step of natural selection!  Here you will find a plthora of activities with Martini Lunches, lollipop-alcoholic natural selections, carbon based libations, swimsuit parties with contests and conseling on the future and the past.  Stop in, say hi and explore your own evolution.
fields.name: Martini Village

fields.description: Meanderthals- "Survival of the Fittest, caveman style".  Come battle it out physically with the "Caveman Joust" or mentally with "Giant Jang-off", and find out if you have what it takes to evolve.
fields.name: Meanderthals

fields.description: Medusa is an open, fun and creative space dedicated to everything Jellyfish... Join us as we celebrate the creature that found its evolutionary groove over 650 million years ago. Activities taking place in our pulsating "Jellie Bloom Dome" include the Ms. Medusa Pageant, afternoon tea dances & more.
fields.name: Medusa

fields.description: Three simple three-sided wooden pyramids in a triangular orientation which will be built upon, interconnected, and decorated over the course of the week with lumber, found materials, and fabrics. This will essentially "evolove" over the week as people add onto it, going along with the main theme.
fields.name: Metamorph

fields.description: Roll into the Midnight Ridazz camp for bike blessings from our Ordained Ministers, maintain your motive self sufficiency with mentored DIY bicycle repair, join us on organized cycle tours and stick around for some sexy, sexy bike talk.
fields.name: Midnight Ridazz

fields.description: Roll into the Midnight Ridazz camp for bike blessings from our Ordained Ministers, maintain your motive self sufficiency with mentored DIY bicycle repair, join us on organized cycle tours and stick around for some sexy, sexy bike talk.
fields.name: Midnight Ridazz

fields.description: The Mind Shaft Society is a collaboration of artistic scientists. We go on an Expedition every winter, then recreate and present the findings at Burning Man every year.
fields.name: Mind Shaft Society

fields.description: The smallest yet most expressive piece of facial hair. The classic disguise. The brother of the monocle. The cousin of the soul patch. The perfect accompaniment to the mystery of man. Signaling to the world that something is hidden but hinted. Concealed and yet revealed. Close your eyes and remember the magic of play and the power of possibility.
fields.name: Ministry of the Magical Mustache

fields.description: Miracle Fruit Camp brings a "taste-full" element to BRC. Think cold, fruity, refreshing sweetness falling from the sky and into your mouth during the hottest part of the day while being fanned, spritz’d and told how wonderful you are by pleasant pranksters wearing Carmen Miranda hats.
fields.name: Miracle Fruit Camp

fields.description: Here to serve for our 5th year, welcome to Mischief Camp! Mischief Camp is the only spot on the Esplanade to feature live video feeds from across the playa. Come look for yourself and see parts of the city you’ve never seen before.  Come play our shocking reaction & skill games. Out on the town looking for something to do? Bring your friends over to Mischief Bar.
fields.name: Mischief Camp

fields.description: In the theory of evolution MiscreAnt Hill aims to take the communal camp experience to the next level by manufacturing a unique canvas shade structure to focus our antics under one rooftop. We bring the music, the weird, and the creativity, all in the spirit of MisAdventure.
fields.name: MiscreAnt Hill

fields.description: Savor the flavors of San Francisco's Mission district out on the playa....Pretentious coffees interspersed with greasy gorditas, high octane sangria, Latin Beats and cheap Mexican beer. And don't miss our 5th Annual Sangria SoundClash Party on Thursday @ 4:20 for bottomless Sangria and Latin beats.
fields.name: Mission Country Club

fields.description: When the sun reaches its zenith and is beating down on the citizens of Black Rock City, head over to the coolest Bedouin Palace on the playa and relax with an ice cold martini while lounging on pillows and poufs. Peruse our book of true erotic stories and if the spirit moves you write one yourself.
fields.name: Mohammeds Mini Martini and Erotica

fields.description: The Wigs welcome you to our home, Monticello, an epicenter of unbridled debauchery, pseudo-aristocratic absurdism, unfathomable sexiness, and pantaloon-shaking madness.
fields.name: Monticello

fields.description: When the Full Moon shines upon Yosemite Falls, the Moonbow there, creates a special place of quiet reflection that represents America's great parks and Nature. We're campers and activists that will have quiet space, yoga, crystal singing bowls, a gay pride parade for todays evolving gay community.
fields.name: Moonbow Camp

fields.description: After focusing on integrated theme camps for many years, Moonrock has decided to expand its field of vision and bring the playa a spectrum of smaller wonderful units: an interactive and multifunctional art vehicle, community workshops, bad ideas, and a fierce dedication to heckling and shenanigans.
fields.name: Moonrock

fields.description: Graceful grazing lands for a modest myriad of mootopians and whomever might meander by, we nestle next to blazing daytime beats and roam in search of nighttime feats, always eager to wander into the great moo yonder and discover delicious adventures for all.
fields.name: Mootopia

fields.description: This camp is like talking to your mom, only with more laughs and less guilt. Join these smart, sassy apron-wearing moms for some lemonade and cookies and chat about love, life and bucket lists.  Take home a self-decorated ''bucket-list-on-a-bag" or help with our "Evolution of the Bra'' art project.
fields.name: Mothers of InVENTion

fields.description: They came from Sea to Land, from the Uncharted Depths of Lake Lahotan, to the open Playa just to serve you frosty cold beverages! The Mudskippers will be serving primordial beverages and Fortune Readings at the Mudskipper Cafe, and at Camp Celestial Bodies Bar!
fields.name: Mudskipper Cafe

fields.description:
Believe the unbelievable! Explore the unexplored! View fantastic alternative lifeforms in relative safety! Bring a cup.
The Museum of Unnatural History. Mutate now, avoid the rush.
fields.name: Museum of Unnatural History

fields.description: Featuring members of Portland's finest bike-club, Zoobomb, providing Bike Fun to the citizens of Black Rock City. Ride our mutant bicycle creations, compete in our BRC Bike Fair (Wednesday), and learn to ride the Tall-bike obstacle course.
fields.name: Mutant Bikology Camp

fields.description: Mutant Mo's Last Chance Saloon! The most dangerous bar in the universe. No one will look twice at that third arm here, partner. Hey, sometimes even a mutant wants to go where everyone knows its name.
fields.name: Mutant Mo's Last Chance Saloon

fields.description: Come play in our garden of mutations!
fields.name: Mutation/Creation

fields.description: Mystikal Misfits have been on a global journey, observing, identifying, collecting, cataloguing and experimenting with earthly specimens in order to unlock the mysteries of evolution. We are creating our own evolutionary designs to speed up progress. Our camp is our workshop and museum of our work.
fields.name: Mystikal Misfits

fields.description: Nipple Inspection and Placement Station. Coming tp BRC to further advancements in the science of nipple classification. How do your nipples stand up? Come by to have your nipples evaluated for type and class. Nipple coverings will be given as needed while supplies last.
fields.name: N.I.P.S.

fields.description:
NYC Container Camp is the New York container filled with all the love, joy,
art and creativity shipped from the other side of the country! Come get your
goods and sit awhile for our evening drinks while putting together your bikes and art and maybe even play mailbox baseball!
fields.name: NYC Container Camp

fields.description: An urban oasis with NY based Kostume Kult and Squid Row with PRED from East Davis, CA.  Daytime kostume dome transformations with interactive art, absurdity and activities on both the Esplanade and Avenue A. See camp listings for more...
fields.name: NYrvana Village

fields.description: Our sneakniess is something to be seen! Come by on Monday or Thursday afternoon for an afternoon libation in the shade and check out the debut of the Purple People Eater mutant vehicle while it is in playa-dock.
fields.name: Naked Ninjas

fields.description: Nectar Village is about you. It is about what you need… to survive, refuel, and revitalize. Mind, body and spirit are all served, and you’ll find the nectar you seek for any of them, in the camps at our oasis. Offerings continuously from 8am to 10pm.
fields.name: Nectar Village

fields.description:
New Jersey
HEY go F%?& yourself!  Jersey's known for it's unique style of hospitality, and we welcome all travelers. Stop by, hang out in our pyramids, tell us a story - just don't ask us what exit we're from. Fuggeddaboutit!
fields.name: New Jersey

fields.description: New Warrior Camp:  Sacred magical space for new warriors and their friends.
fields.name: New Warrior Camp

fields.description: Come visit, party, get misted and take photos of your friends as they evolve as part of our evolution mural. Also take rides on our 4 person, 4 wheel peddle cart.
fields.name: Nice Nice

fields.description: Ten years ago, a ninja commando unit was sent to prison for a crime they didn't commit. These ninjas escaped from a maximum security prison and now survive as soldiers of fortune. If you have a problem, if no one else can help, and if you can find them, maybe you can hire...Ninjas and Beer!
fields.name: Ninjas and Beer...

fields.description: Providing a soothing Northwest atmosphere to escape the mid-day heat, step through the Northwest Mist portal and transcend the heat of the day for a momentary refreshening. We are also the home of the ghost of The Lady Washington residing in the Redirection Connection Village.
fields.name: Northwest Mist

fields.description: Camp Nose Fish returns in 2009 to present two new theme-related interactive projects: Tree of Life and Superhero Evolution.  We'll help you evolve into the superhero you are by helping you create your own costume, and at night you control a 15 foot tree of light with your fingers.
fields.name: Nose Fish

fields.description: New dome!  Bar, lounge, hammocks!  Non-stop aural refreshment--a soundscape of a variety of species--from jb to john phillip sousa.  Marshmallows.
fields.name: Nothing Works

fields.description: OMCC is the Object Manipulation Concentration Camp where spinners and jugglers can be found all day and night honing their craft and teaching their skills.  Workshops every day and drop in lessons any time on poi, staff, hoop, balls, clubs, fans, you name it.
fields.name: OMCC

fields.description: Oasis camp provides water, lemonade and other liquids during our daily siestas throughout the week as well as a cool, welcoming place to relax. Also make sure to come by for our Maritime Ball!
fields.name: Oasis Camp

fields.description: Retreat from the heat and the dust inside Ocean's Serene Luxury Spa @ Stardust Lounge Casino. Pamper your skin with a rejuvenating seaweed facial mask, beautify your body with a unique temporary tattoo, or simply hang out for some nautical arts & crafts with our lovely mermaids and saucy sailors.
fields.name: Ocean's Serene

fields.description: Organic cider and other related activities from the wild woods of Northern California: the Raven flies, the great Elk bellows, and Apples hang from laden Trees.  Drink and make merry for the Fenris Wolf draws nigh!
fields.name: Oden's Eye Apple Cider

fields.description: Oobleck invites you to challenge your senses! Play with oobleck, a non-Newtonian fluid made from corn starch and water - it drips down your arm but won't splash when punched. Oobleck hangs with Tasty Noodles, a fabulous desert party crew packing a bar, amplified sound and misters.
fields.name: Oobleck

fields.description: Dark, Sleazy, and Alcohol-Fueled.  We're still slinging bloody marys this year but not quite so goddamn early!
fields.name: Opulent DETH Temple

fields.description: Overmind. A place to remember your hidden past and prepare for your journey into the future of human consciousness. Come during the day and we'll "space out" your costume for your voyage through the cosmos. Come at night we'll be telling danceable audio-visual stories about origins and destinations.
fields.name: Overmind

fields.description: Camp Pagena is Place where all the evolution of the old and new worlds unite.A place where all people of colour creed and culture can come together as one in union and place their very own journey of evolution through our unique PANGEA map. A place where cultural diversity will touch all the senses.
fields.name: PANGEA

fields.description: PEX returns with that invisible vibe. We will be back with the stage, shade structure with daily yoga classes and Arche-Dream for Humankind.
fields.name: PEX

fields.description: Photogartho is an interactive photography studio/gallery and chill spot where you can have your souvenir portrait taken of you in your playa finest whilst being served a refreshing drink by Miss Lemonada/Fresca.
fields.name: PHOTOGARTHO

fields.description: PLAYA MAGIC featuring Close-up Magic of THOMAS of Carson Valley, Nevada.  He will be performing 3 shows daily in an air conditioned, dust free zone.  30 minute show in the day who and one 40 minute evening show. You may request his appearance at your venue upon inspection.
fields.name: PLAYA MAGIC

fields.description: The Echo People return to run the Reflection (Wall-of-Lights) Dance Club & Bar at the "PPR." Come entertain us with your rhythmic dance moves, maybe we'll give you a special elixir or honor. Learn the secret word of the day, feel the Monolith – have you evolved? Make contact at the 'Copy Cat' party.
fields.name: PPR: The Prod Pump and Rest

fields.description: Preserved In Time is a camp that is within Barbie Death Village. This camp is where you seal what you want in a 3.oz. can, then create a label the tells you what is in your can, or you just open it in the future and have a surprise.
fields.name: PRESERVED IN TIME

fields.description: PUREPLAYA is a place were we except what is, while realizing anything is possible!  It is a place of creativity, transformation, and sharing.  We offer a 'pure' platform to the playa where anything can happen!  Come participate in this experiment with us!   Confused?  Great, hope to see you soon!
fields.name: PUREPLAYA

fields.description: A cool heathen oasis, we at Pan's Garden provide organic garden lessons, libations, and brilliantly painted canvases with bright LED lighting. Whether you need tips for wiring solar panels, suggestions on running drip systems & compost for your home gardens, or a drink in the shade -come visit us!
fields.name: Pan's Garden

fields.description: Serving cold Tiki punch to BRC residents, aged 21+ only, in a cool relaxing clothing optional environment. You don’t have to remove your clothes to enjoy this nudist bar. Come by for event schedule then for happy hour, you may get “leid”, and party with us. Be LNT friendly and bring your own cup.
fields.name: Party Naked Tiki Bar

fields.description:
We are a full service Pee Funnel Camp, dispensing Pee Funnels to ladies (or
gentlemen) at any time of day or night!  Pee Funnels allow ladies to easily
stand and pee or aim into a jug.
fields.name: Pee Funnel Camp

fields.description:
Feeling a little sinister, some hatred and despair?
Adultery, debauchery, ya we’ve all been there.
Incest, lust and greed, all the evils that we do,
Soon to become the Portrait of Dorian,
But is it Dorian, or is it you?

Artists are invited to create the “Portraits of Dorian.”
fields.name: People's Art Congress (PAC)

fields.description:
Kick up your feet and recharge your adventurous spirit in our extra cool and
shady oasis while enjoying henna art, chilled Moroccan mint tea, misting bottles, and Turkish tobacco.
fields.name: Persian Excursion

fields.description:
Petting ZOO welcomes newcomers and only hopes to share the experiences of the playa all while offering an array of creative cocktails, ice-cold bubbling brew, imbibing beverages, and our classic and exclusive 'moon juice'.

Daytime Only. 21 and Over. Donations Accepted.
fields.name: Petting ZOO

fields.description: The Philadelphia Experiment Village is a Community of Camps representing a broad range of international influences. We are uniting the Original PEX Camp with Putt Putt Playa (PPP), Camp Chillax (Los Angeles) The Museum of Unnatural History (NYC) and BBC Camp (U.K. L.A.)
fields.name: Philadelphia Experiment Village

fields.description:
Black Light Art setting, KINO_DOME chill-out at night and "Russian BAR" at day, 
"Psybotik" parties of Techno/Minimal/Brakes/Full-On...
our famous smoothie hour, workshops,lectures and most importantly our NYC-based vibrant international community!
fields.name: Phoenix Circle Village

fields.description: Join us at Pi Camp for thoughtful conversation and engaging discussion of all things scientific.  Come to learn, to teach, to be intrigued and to be awed by SCIENCE.  Bringing pie to share is highly encouraged!
fields.name: Pi Camp

fields.description: Picasso Camp is back! We've got fresh paint, fresh canvasses, and fresh vibes for the playa. Always a participant's best friend, our camp provides Burners a place to express their ideas on two huge canvasses 24/7. Our FUBAR is stocked and ready to serve and our crew of eclectic DJs set the mood. Our chill domes provide the space to create and collaborate!
fields.name: Picasso Camp

fields.description: Fresh, cold, crisp pickles and spicy Pickle-tinis served night and day, from your friends at Ye Olde Pickle Joint.
fields.name: Pickle Joint

fields.description: Make your way to Pigmalions Camp, where each morning, opposable-hooved servers offer a daily dose of delicious bacon. Prepare to squeeel for your Bacon and Bloody Marys - served each day, 11ish in the morning.  PIGMALIONS:  Opposable Hooves Are In
fields.name: Pigamilions: Opposable Hooves

fields.description: Pillowasis is a cushioned respite for the weary traveler.
fields.name: Pillowasis

fields.description:
Pink Mammoth is a not for profit house music and creative arts collective
based in San Francisco. Pink Mammoth is above all a community, one that
nurtures, encourages, and supports its participants in being and in learning
to express themselves.
fields.name: Pink Mammoth

fields.description: Art, Music, Performance, and Bunnies!
fields.name: Pixelstad

fields.description: This is Planet Earth!  Looking for an alternative to techno/electronica?  Come kick it old school with the Black Rock city's 80's Dance Club.  New Wave, Synth, Goth, Industrial, One Hit Wonders.  We have it all, plus 300 of your favorite 80's videos in stereophonic wonder!
fields.name: Planet Earth

fields.description: Come for the mini-golf, stay for the good spirits, leave on one of our art cars!
fields.name: Playa Del Fuego Country Club

fields.description: Come to Playa Go Round at 2:30 & Esplanade. With every rotation you spin into your Dreams & your future flashes before you while beats fill the ether. We are always open and you are always welcome! DJs from Denver, Seattle,& Reno www.PlayaGoRound.com. PGR presents The Rock Opera www.TheRockOpera.net
fields.name: Playa Go Round

fields.description: Back for another triumphant year! Our mission is to provide a home on the Playa for internationals.  We also host many Fantastic events. Including the now famous Zombie Crawl. We welcome all Internationals who want to join.  So come by and take a trip around the world. No “Drop-Ins”.
fields.name: Playa International

fields.description: The Playa Jazz Cafe is back for it’s 5th year a with live nightly jazz performances and our signature Irish coffee. The Jazz Cafe is a musical sanctuary for the weary playa traveler lost in a sea of electronica. Musicians are encouraged to bring their instruments and help spread the magic of jazz!
fields.name: Playa Jazz Cafe

fields.description: Playapets Camp is a group of people who strongly believe in the beauty of all our companions on our journey as humans.  We especially respect the role our domesticated animals have played along out evolutionary path and seek to honor it.
fields.name: PlayaPets

fields.description: The PlayaGon is an infinite-dimensional hyper-inclusive object containing futurists, scientists, artists, 'free-range synergists', and more.  In this object you'll find minds looking forward, listening inward, and reaching out.  Join us for mind expanding memes, rigorous debate, and good margaritas.
fields.name: Playagon

fields.description: Ladies & Gentlemen, lads & lasses, aunts, uncles & other household pests...Have you experienced chafing of the inner thigh? Dryness of the wenis? Wish you could find true love? Well step on into the Playaneer Emporium & find lotions & potions, goops & elixirs to make your every playa dream come true
fields.name: Playaneer Emporium

fields.description:
The Playawaste Raider camp is an oasis and refuge from the happiness
and organization of the surrounding tranquility of the Playa. An
island of chaos and mayhem festooned with the grisly remains and
effects of those that have bored us.
fields.name: Playawastes Raider Camp

fields.description: In the welcoming shade of Pleasure Garden's Sunscreen Station, we will tempt playa denizens with cold lemonade and sunscreen application. Our goal is to provide the Burning Man community with a little slice of paradise devoted to relaxation and exploration of the pleasures of the senses.
fields.name: Pleasure Garden

fields.description: A serene oasis where you can float in the frequencies created by an intimate crew of sound healers, body workers, and movement therapists.  Whether you come for tea and yoga at sunrise or a didgeridoo treatment by dusk, a visit to our calm dome may be the most relaxing space you'll find at the Burn.
fields.name: Pod of Bliss

fields.description:
PolyParadise has been influencing the Hearts & Minds for the past 10 years.
We are a group of Polyamorists seeking to live our dreams, and this camp is
one manifestation of that. Polyamory involves openness to multiple loving
relatinships.
Join us in a variety of events - Come in from the sun....take a load off your
feet...
fields.name: PolyParadise

fields.description: World renowned as the finest purveyors of Shrimp Tacos. I am requesting that you perform five jumping jacks for reading this.
fields.name: Poppycock

fields.description: Have your default-world situated loved-ones send a message transformed to art to their favorite BRC participant. The intended BRC Citizen will receive message delivered in person. Message can also be sent back to default-world.
fields.name: Postal Telegram Office

fields.description: DE-EVOLVE and join the monkey business @ the Primate Playground. Chill on our astro-grass under a parachute shade tree and upload BM city and art maps to your GPS. Enjoy some Improv-Improv, playground games, monkey art, and even a trickling waterfall. What’s more fun than a barrel full of monkeys!
fields.name: Primate Playground & BRC_GPS

fields.description: What the Garden of Eden would have been like if Burners were in charge!  Many, many blinky lights, music of all sorts, and hot and cold running Primordial Ooze on tap nightly.
fields.name: Primordial Swamp

fields.description: Pro Leisure Tour , Home of the "Couch Potato Research Institute and Darwin Lounge". Classes per schedule , Drinks per order.
fields.name: Pro Leisure Tour

fields.description:
Bringing the Gift of Fire to Humankind since the Dawn of Time! Come
experience the fully immersive Tesseract Mirror Box (Lasers, Blinkies
and Pool Toys, oh my!), enjoy edifying Flow Temple workshops during
the day and join us for nightly fire shows as we liberate the Spirit
of Flame!
fields.name: Prometheatrics

fields.description:
Psychic Taxi provides transportation randomly. Our Random Service Taxis are 
pedal powered rickshaws that ferry travelers to Playa destinations chosen by our psychic drivers. Our Hammock pavilion offers shade and luxurious ease. The pedal powered, Psychic Taxi
Nomadic Cafe is a roving bar.
fields.name: Psychic Taxi

fields.description: You've found the home of the Purple Palace art car and the Purple Parasites.
fields.name: Purple Palace Camp

fields.description: Offering a variety of services to make your kitty purrr. We aim to pamper and please with full body massages, shave and grooming services and other fun things to do. Bring your kitty on by the Pussy Hut and check our posted schedule of fun services. Meow.
fields.name: Pussy Hut

fields.description: PPP is a fully interactive mini golf course for people of all ages, day or night. Stop by and play-a couple rounds... have a friendly competition with your camp mates... relax under our Club House shade structure, listen to chill music.
fields.name: Putt-Putt Playa

fields.description: This is a 40' pendulum swing with the ability to free your mind and heart and return you to a time when your life was much simpler. Remember jumping on a swing and pushing the limits of the swing, it was as if you were flying, free from all your worries. This swing is sure to deliver.
fields.name: Pyramid Scheme the sequel.
Quixotes Presents The Man and Monkey Pub
R&R with Divas on the Playa

fields.description: Robotronia returns for its' 10th attempt as a "theme camp". Hotshot the Robot, Spectral Interactive Video Screens, d6 and Hug02 will be joined this year by The Mantis, Mr. Jellifish, and even a special performance from Zsu-Zsu. Show your (de)evolutionary skills while getting your photo with us in 09.
fields.name: ROBOTRONIA

fields.description: Come sit in the shade of Rub A Dub. Providing chill space, positive dub/reggae music,and Rub-A-Dub atmosphere. Some SF Bay Area Shredders.
fields.name: RUB A DUB

fields.description: We put the ROCK in Black Rock City. Tune in for an eclectic array of music, mayhem and commentary. Theme camps, villages, and artists wishing to make radio announcements about events on the playa are welcome to stop in or contact us by email prior to the event. Celebrating our 10th year on the playa.
fields.name: Radio Electra 89.9 FM

fields.description: If it's Random or Unneccessary, you can find it here, from the Hatfeild/McCoy watergun battle, to really big drinks with really long straws, to domino necklace trading, to info/art on gods and belief of the past. Come by in/with something random and tell us what you would do for a Klondike bar!
fields.name: Random and Unnecessary Camp, The

fields.description: Rathskellar (nee Spike’s Vampire Bar) is a den of mad scientists, libertines and sci-fi/DIY style. Find flavors of Goth/Industrial madness within our dome, libations at our bar, and the hottest playa performers on our stage. We are the dark, sexy and spooky that balances out the endless techno of BRC
fields.name: Rathskellar

fields.description: Rave'Ns Nest a place for good music, fun and refreshment.
fields.name: Rave'Ns Nest

fields.description: Welcome to the 2nd year of Redirection Connection Village! Drop in for a ride on one of the many Mutant Vehicles docked at the new hub/loading station for the Un-Official Public Transit System of BRC and get Connected for Redirection to another location on the playa!
fields.name: Redirection Connection

fields.description: At the Relaxomatic Plushitorium, you will find a madcap roller coaster ride of tranquility and repose -- If it's soft, squishy, and fun to sit on, you'll probably find it here. Additionally register here to send your grilled Cheese-o-grams to your friends and enemies.
fields.name: Relaxomatic Plushitorium

fields.description: Helping costume BRC since 1998. Do you need bridesmaids for your playa wedding, or are looking for the perfect outfit for that party? ASK US! From frumpy to fabulous, we have you covered.
fields.name: Reno Housewives

fields.description:
RhythmWave theme camp is dedicated to the practice of dance as a moving meditation, an expression of who we are in each evolving moment. 
Everyone at Burning Man is invited to our shaded bamboo dance floor to participate in 2-3 sets of ecstatic dance daily, as well as yoga & meditation.
fields.name: RhythmWave

fields.description:
RISA is just like the resort planet from Star Trek, renowned for its breezes
and easy-going, uninhibited sexuality. Our main attraction at Risa this year
is the Peacock Shuttle. Look for Risa and the Shuttle
within Redirection Connection Village!
fields.name: Risa

fields.description: The Roarax Rounge in conjunction with delightful derelicts at the Hammock Hangout ask you to come by and SING, nay, ROAR your heart out with us at either our Roving Karaoke Destruction Unit, The Roar Shack or in the Shady Comfort of the Hammock Hangout!
fields.name: Roarax Rounge

fields.description: What happens when a giant robot awakens from its slumber beneath the earth during a weeklong art festival featuring 50,000 humans? Answer: Its robot friends throw a huge party! :)
fields.name: Robosapiens

fields.description: A global, lo-key crew that rocks great sounds with ghetto tech beats and a street fab attitude. We're bringing awesome to the playa with BIG, clean sound, LED visuals, and new media art, featuring djs from NYC, SF, Hong Kong, London and more. Find us on the playa by following your Robot Heart.
fields.name: Robot Heart

fields.description: Sometimes you have to hit Rock Bottom and begin again.  8 years ago Rock Bottom was one of 3 camps who formed The Deep End.  Though the Deep End is now playa legend, some AARP members will gather for a more intimate celebration of high spirits and deep grooves.  Stop in, bring a bottle, and dance.
fields.name: Rock Bottom

fields.description:
From Seattle, we are a small family of orphans with a lot to offer.
Come join us for:
"The RockStar Treatment" (haircut,facial,footscrub,icedtea,reiki,massage),
Sinner Chair, where your playa sins are zapped away
And Ambient Live Music each evening.
You will come away revived and energized!
fields.name: RockStar Orphans

fields.description: NEO@ROOT SOCIETY-Chapter 34:2009 - GI Syndrome(greed and irresponsibility)wiped out mankind except for a glowing group of survivors on the desert grid.  Drawn by the powerful BIG DOMES Force-NEO@ROOT SOCIETY promises truth in the future beats of our emerging civilization. Something large is looming!
fields.name: Root Society

fields.description: At Rubber Chicken Camp we delight in the celebration of the Rubber Chicken. The camp is made up of artists working on the playa art installations, Eighth Wonder and The Watch. Information about the art installations will be available and there will be a Rubber Chicken social event on Tuesday evening.
fields.name: Rubber Chicken Camp

fields.description: Dedicated to saying goodbye to those that affected our lives so profoundly the Rue Morgue helps that process by teaching people to fold origami and placing the final art into our Playatech Goffins for their final destination "a temple burn". At night we dance macabre New Orleans style!
fields.name: Rue Morgue

fields.description: S'mores are not just a camping food, but a social experience. Come join us for S'mores every night at sundown then gather around the fire for campfire cheer and meeting new friends. Campfire singers and entertainers get a special surprise. Warning: marshmallows will get burned! S'mores 7-9 pm nightly
fields.name: S'mores n Amour

fields.description: SHIFT Camp is large, friendly, and devoted to evolving consciousness and having fun. We have a hot bar, talks, performances, comedy, and a cool dome for dancing. Presenters this year include Annie Harrison; Daniel Pinchbeck; Lorenzo Hagerty; Carolyn Garcia; and Amanda Feilding, Countess of Wemyss.
fields.name: SHIFT

fields.description: SHIFT Camp is large, friendly, and devoted to evolving consciousness and having fun. We have a hot bar, talks, performances, comedy, and a cool dome for dancing. Presenters this year include Annie Harrison; Daniel Pinchbeck; Lorenzo Hagerty; Carolyn Garcia; and Amanda Feilding, Countess of Wemyss.
fields.name: SHIFT

fields.description: Remember SPIN ART? We have created a four foot diameter, solar powered machine for you to create your own artwork and bring it home. We have core board canvas or take off your shirt and make a one-of-a-kind Burning Man Masterpiece. All are welcome daily from 3PM to 6PM.
fields.name: SPIN ART CAMP

fields.description: Stamp Camp is dedicated to create community and friendship while entertaining others with our array of rubber stamp body art.
fields.name: STAMP CAMP

fields.description: Sacred Spaces Village comprises of mystics, artists, healers, and revolutionaries who are passionate about creating sacred spaces on and off the playa through visionary art, ceremony, teaching, and healing work.
fields.name: Sacred Spaces Village

fields.description: Source of all your playa safer sex needs: condoms, lube, gloves, and plastic wrap for dams.  All kits are free, not for sale, not for barter.  Look for Outpost Bags.  Also, Erotic Fetish Wear from Rubber Inner Tubes(See What When Where) & Women's Only Liquid Latex Body Painting (Fri 11:00am -3:40pm.
fields.name: Safer Sex Camp

fields.description: When the sun starts to set our 8 foot tall tubes of dry-ice cooled sake are awakened by beats from NightJuice, our velvety, pulsating art car. Come dance and be refreshed by our ice cold sake.
fields.name: Sake Watering Hole

fields.description: Sakénoma, Black Rock's nearly famous Saké-Bar, invites you to visit them during the hottest part of the day for the coldest Saké on the Playa. Kanpai!
fields.name: Sakenoma

fields.description: Sala Of Unnamed Love holds space for sacred, movement & healing arts on the playa.  Get your meditation & yoga on, your capoeira Angola craftiness, and your games and exercises for being in the now and speaking from the heart.  And if you wanna instruct, let S.O.U.L. hear from you soon.
fields.name: Sala Of Unnamed Love

fields.description: Ever wonder what the child in you is thinking/feeling/wanting? Play in a sandbox with little toys to find out more about your Self, or at least to think in symbols instead of words.
fields.name: Sandbox Camp

fields.description:
Chess Kamp is Back:
Challenge your chess skills in a symbolic battle of ideological opposites, using figurative chess pieces on a 4’x4’ chess board. Play the ultimate game of chess, pitting images of Evolutionary and sociological hope (Science, free thinking) against superstitious Creationism!
fields.name: Science Vs Superstition: ChessKamp

fields.description: Hometown:  New York, NY
fields.name: Scotch & Hop

fields.description: "Semuta" is mentioned several times in the Frank Herbert "Dune" novels, but never in much detail.  It is described as a drug addiction that requires both a specific drug ("semuta") and a specific type of music ("semuta music") to work. Without the music, the drug is apparently fairly useless, but the combination of the two produces "sustained, timeless ecstasy."
fields.name: Semuta Lounge

fields.description: Sexy Trampoline...Come jump on our Sexy Trampoline and then have a cold beverage to cool your jets. The second rule of Sexy Trampoline is if it's your first time at Sexy Trampoline...you must jump!
fields.name: Sexy Trampoline

fields.description: Burning Man can be pretty intense: the people, the music, the motion, the heat... our goal is to provide an escape from all of that. A shady, cozy nook on the playa where you can take a yoga class, meditate, or enjoy a peaceful breakfast.
fields.name: Shady Waffle

fields.description: Join us in a journey to find your power animal; to recover that lost soul you left with your ex:  to clear the door to your great cosmic dance:  and we protect you from most everything:::: but yourself:
fields.name: Shaman Dome

fields.description: Shipwreck tiki Lounge. An actual vintage wood sailboat beached upon the rocks of a forbidden isle. Join the castaways for afternoon grog at their exotic tiki bar of hand made idols, gods and flaming totems. Beware of cannibals!
fields.name: Shipwreck tiki Lounge

fields.description: "What happens in Sin City stays in Sin City." Sin City is a place where freedom of expression is embraced. There are many things to see and do at Party Naked Tiki Bar, Playfully Yours, Club BamBam and much more. Come and check out our village schedule of happenings for planned events.
fields.name: Sin City

fields.description:
The Sinister Minister will ask for confessions, give penances, offer communion, and may accept indulgences.  Only the creative and truly perverse will pass - others will need to seek their life on another path. The lucky few will see the Bearded Child Film Festival. 
Camp will be operational Wed thru Fri from 2000 to 2200.  The Bearded Child Film Festival will be on Sat night starting after the burn.
fields.name: Sinister Minister

fields.description: Regroup and relax at the teahouse with Skinny and friends, a refuge from the unse, unse, unse, providing a  baby grand piano, space for performing, music, conversation, funk, art, copeira, and serving tea 24/7.  We are reliquarians.
fields.name: Skinny Kitty Teahouse

fields.description: Hey fish-man! Khakis also seemed like a good idea to the troglodytes but this is the playa. Time to evolve! Let our sirens, satyrs and seamstresses soothe you with sinful fashions to excite your passions. We have the racks to put you back in the reproductive stack. Dance! Drink! Dress-The-Fuck-Up!
fields.name: Slutgarden

fields.description:
Snow Koan Solar provides solar-based power for burners who need to recharge anything from a camera battery to an art car.  We also serve chilly refreshments each afternoon when the sun is four fingers from the horizon.  Our motto:   Relax  Recharge  Rethink.  
Consider stopping by.
fields.name: Snow Koan Solar

fields.description: SNOWFLAKE VILLAGE, now in it's tenth year, encompasses people from the Midwest, Canada, and around the world. Take an exotic instant vacation, hook up at Playa Speed Dating, visit a movie theater, ride an art car, interact with 24/7 sculptures and games...all in one place!
fields.name: Snowflake Village

fields.description: Come down to our level to beat the heat of the day & to dance the night away. Enjoy Ice Tea & Sangria at our bar, add your touch to community art project "Hey Baby, What's your Sign?" and enjoy rockin’ DJ's, bands,& performers. At nightfall scenes from BRC will be projected high above camp.
fields.name: South of All Borders
